# Assets and Build Workflow

- Build tooling: Vite with Tailwind CSS v4 (see [vite.config.mjs](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/vite.config.mjs), [package.json](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/package.json)).
- Entrypoints:
  - JS: [resources/js/app.js](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/resources/js/app.js)
  - CSS: [resources/css/app.css](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/resources/css/app.css), [resources/css/editor-style.css](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/resources/css/editor-style.css)
- Tailwind v4 usage:
  - `@import 'tailwindcss'` in CSS; additional theme layers in [app.css](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/resources/css/app.css)
  - `@source` globs include TailPress PHP to capture class usage
- Commands:
  - Dev server: `npm run dev` (Vite)
  - Production build: `npm run build` â†’ outputs to `themes/aratavietnam/dist/` with manifest
- Base path is set for build to `/wp-content/themes/aratavietnam/dist/` in [vite.config.mjs](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/vite.config.mjs).
- Keep selectors/IDs consistent with templates. Example: if toggling the main menu in [app.js](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/resources/js/app.js), ensure corresponding IDs/classes exist in [header.php](mdc:themes/aratavietnam/header.php).
